Project Overview:
This project investigates long-term changes in the structure of the consumer basket in Ukraine from 1950 to 2023. 
The analysis focuses on identifying historical trends, shifts in expenditure patterns, and changes in consumer priorities over time.

Tools:
- Microsoft Excel
- Statistical Analysis
- Economic Data Analysis
- Data Visualization
Methods Applied:
- Historical data collection and preparation
- Trend analysis
- Comparative analysis across time periods
- Structure and dynamics assessment
- Visualization of expenditure categories
- Interpretation of long-term economic changes

Results:
The project identifies significant changes in consumer spending patterns over more than seven decades. 
The analysis highlights the impact of economic, social, and market transformations on household consumption and provides insights into the evolution of consumer behavior in Ukraine.
